### Overview

This indicator tracks the extent of tree canopy cover in the region, as measured by the National Forest Inventory (NFI). Tree canopy cover is an important aspect of urban greening, biodiversity and climate resilience. The NFI source [dataset](https://data-forestry.opendata.arcgis.com/datasets/d62fd97664a64596844b9834c1737e46_0/explore) is filtered by the "Woodland" category and clipped to the boundary of the West of England to provide a regional measure of the area covered by woodland.


